English articles can be tricky, especially if your native language doesnâ€™t have them. The main articles are â€œaâ€, â€œanâ€ (indefinite articles) and â€œtheâ€ (definite article). Thereâ€™s also the case of using no article (sometimes called the â€œzero articleâ€). Hereâ€™s how to use them:
â€¢	â€œaâ€ vs â€œanâ€ (Indefinite Articles):
â€¢	Use â€œaâ€ before words that start with a consonant sound. Use â€œanâ€ before words that start with a vowel sound[65]. The key is the sound, not just the letter.
o	â€œa dogâ€, â€œa carâ€, â€œa big universityâ€ (note: â€œuniversityâ€ starts with /j/ sound â€œyooâ€, which is a consonant sound, so â€œa universityâ€[65]).
