â€¢	These mean one of something (not specific which one)[66]. Use them only with singular countable nouns (you canâ€™t say â€œa waterâ€ â€“ water isnâ€™t countable; youâ€™d say â€œsome waterâ€ or just â€œwaterâ€).
â€¢	General use of a/an (Indefinite):
