Chapter 16: Phrasal Verbs for Natural Speech
Learning Section
Phrasal verbs are verbs combined with one or two particles (prepositions/adverbs) that create a new meaning (e.g., â€œfind out,â€ â€œpick up,â€ â€œget alongâ€). They are extremely common in everyday English and often replace more formal verbs. Here are 10 essential phrasal verbs and how to use them:
1.	get up â€“ to rise from bed or from a seated position.
Example: â€œI get up at 7 AM every day.â€ (wake and leave bed)
â€œPlease donâ€™t get up, I can find the exit myself.â€ (donâ€™t stand on my account)
